    <h1>Shelburne Public Library Welcomes You </h1>
      <p><img src="art/libraryimage-featherededges.jpg" width="240" height="141" align="left" /> Shelburne Public Library provides access to a rich and diverse variety of materials to meet the informational and recreational needs of the community. </p>
      <p> The library serves the community of Shelburne and the surrounding townships of Amaranth, Melancthon, Mono, and Mulmur. People who work or attend school in Shelburne are also welcome to join our library. </p>
      <p>The collection itself is comprised of over 32,000 items including popular fiction and non-fiction titles, local historical materials, reference material, DVDs, music CDs, books on CD, magazines and newspapers. Internet access on computers, wireless connectivity, children's literacy computers and access and support on a large variety of informational databases are all part of the services provided by your library.</p>
      <p align="center"><img src="art/mandate.jpg" width="454" height="89" /></p>
      <h2><strong>New Collection Services </strong></h2>      <p>You can access the Library Collection online through the KOHA system; patrons can place holds and renew materials online. With funding support from the Ministry of Culture through Knowledge Ontario and the Southern Ontario Library System (SOLS), we now provide access to more than 30 informational e-resources. These include databases for research, health, car repairs, genealogy, literature and children's research and recreation. We also have available e-audio books for you to download to your ipod or MP3 Player. </p>
      <p>Our programs include children's story time and activities and an ever expanding variety of programs such as Spanish lessons, Book Club, Genealogy research and collection based interest events such as Cooking up a Mystery@ the Library. Our meeting rooms are available for rent to the community for events and activities. </p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
      <p>&nbsp;</p>
